Hello,

My collaborators and I are considering submitting our R package for single-cell CRISPR screen data analysis to Bioconductor (package website <https://katsevich-lab.github.io/sceptre/> and e-book <https://timothy-barry.github.io/sceptre-book/>). We have several questions about the suitability of our package for Bioconductor and changes that we might need to implement to make our package more consistent with Bioconductor package guidelines. Would a member of the Bioconductor team be available for a brief (30-60 minute) Zoom call to discuss these issues? We would very much appreciate the help.

Thank you greatly,
